<div class="image-container aligncenter"><img src="http://kaktuskontainer.wdfiles.com/local--files/lurk-work-dos/access_4.png" width="500px" alt="access_4.png" class="image" /></div>
<p>At first it looked like a whole lot of still air. The back wall could not even be made out. Suddenly there was the distinct croak of Sage from the other side of the bulkhead.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>CROAK</em></strong></p>
<p>Emily used her hand to hold a finger up to Umber in hopes that he is able to quiet the toad who has literally been croaking every other minute since being down in the sub-level.</p>
<p>&quot;That's better.&quot; She whispered to herself.</p>
<p>The suddenly there was the unmistakable sound of patter coming out from the dark. Emily squinted to see if her vision could cut through the blackness as something started to emerge.</p>
